were little changed at CDollars 3.6bn. Central Capital, a troubled financial
services group placed under court supervision on June 15, will be 90 per
cent controlled by creditors through a new holding company when
restructuring of the group is completed.
The remaining 10 per cent will be held by preferred and common shareholders,
including Mr Leonard Ellen and his associates, who previously had 60 per
cent control.
