<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 92 / Management (The Growing Business): Taking research in your
Stride - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Organisations in areas of industrial decline can meet up to half of their
research and development costs under an Pounds 11.5m European Community
programme known as Science and Technology for Regional Innovation and
Development in Europe (Stride).
Grants are available for projects which:
encourage small and medium-sized businesses to make use of the services and
skills of institutions of higher education and other research centres;
expand local centres set up to support innovation and technology transfer;
promote regional R&amp;D activity;
and help education and training activities intended to promote the other
three areas. Small firms pursuing their own R&amp;D programmes are not eligible.
Contact regional DTI offices and the Welsh and Scottish Offices.
</TEXT>
