of just Pounds 2m in the year to March. It has since taken steps to cut its
cost base, notably through the ending of services to Shrewsbury, Shropshire;
Cleethorpes, Humberside; and Blackpool, Lancashire.
The marketing campaign is believed to include a relaunch of the scheme
offering free travel to shoppers collecting vouchers from Boots stores, and
a revamp of the Silver Standard service for holders of full-fare standard
class tickets.
