<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S actuarial profession was urged yesterday to help tackle the
marketing crisis affecting the life assurance industry.
Mr Roger Laker of Ernst &amp; Young, the accountancy firm, said actuaries had
been 'too reluctant to intrude into an area of business which is
traditionally run by others'.
