FT  15 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Sharpe &amp; Fisher continues recovery
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARPE &amp; FISHER, the building supplies and property company, reported
pre-tax profits of Pounds 420,000 for the half year to end-June. Sales rose
by Pounds 728,000 to Pounds 22.1m.
The outcome compared with losses of Pounds 436,000 in last year's first
half; the company returned to the black in the second six months.
The main reason for the upturn was the turnround in the building supplies
division, which achieved profits of Pounds 319,000 against a loss of Pounds
252,000.
Property also improved with a 13.5 per cent increase to Pounds 771,000.
Earnings emerged at 1.5p per share (1.4p losses) and the interim dividend is
unchanged at 1.5p.
Mr Charles Fisher, chairman and chief executive, said he had no reason to be
opti-mistic about the prospect of economic recovery in the short term.
Interest rates were still too high to promote any improvement in sales, he
added.
