working life in Zambia, attracted attention by moving there and establishing
four estates to grow cotton and food stuffs. Part of the job entailed
recruiting a security force some 1,500 men strong.
Hewlett has also presumably had several recent visits from Lonrho chief
executive Tiny Rowland, who has played a part in negotiating the peace
agreement in Mozambique.
