<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 92 / Clinton launches national voter registration drive
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GOVERNOR Bill Clinton (above left) launched at the weekend a national voter
registration drive, to be led by the Rev Jesse Jackson (above right), in an
attempt to add thousands of black voters to the rolls in the hope they will
support the Democratic presidential ticket, AP reports from Washington.
But questions remain as to whether relations between the men have warmed in
the wake of Mr Jackson's complaints of a 'push-off' strategy by the Clinton
campaign. Mr Jackson sought to add the first unregistered voters to the roll
during the seventh annual Black Family Reunion in Washington, saying the
vote 'has so much power'.
The event is sponsored by the National Council of Negro Women to draw
attention to problems suffered by black families.
''Clinton campaign workers said the registration drive would include 300
events in 30 cities.
