FT  14 SEP 92 / Construction Contracts: British embassy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
YEOMANS &amp; PARTNERS, a P&amp;O company, has been awarded a Pounds 450,000
contract to refurbish the British Embassy in Jakarta, Indonesia, for the
Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office.
Work has already started to replace electrical installations, suspended
ceilings and partitions within the embassy which will remain occupied and
fully operational throughout the duration of the project.
Yeomans' success in Jakarta follows a series of shopfitting contracts in
Czechoslovakia where it has fitted out two carpet and soft furnishing
stores.
